fields.name: attempt_start_msec
fields.description: Time when the attempt starts. CQ calculates this by searching for the last 'The CQ bit checked by...' message, which corresponds to the moment when the user has clicked on the CQ checkbox

fields.name: first_start_msec
fields.description: The time when CQ actually start processing the patch (first start message).

fields.name: last_start_msec
fields.description: The time when last start message was posted.

fields.name: first_stop_msec
fields.description: The time when first stop message was posted

fields.name: last_stop_msec
fields.description: The time when CQ stopped processing the patchset (last stop message). This is when attempt ends.

fields.name: committed
fields.description: True if the patch was committed in this attempt.

fields.name: was_throttled
fields.description: True if the request was throttled due to too many CLs being committed.

fields.name: waited_for_tree
fields.description: True if the request had to wait for an open tree.
